{"lemma":"سَلِسٌ","slug":"سَلِسٌ","root":"س.ل.س","root_slug":"س-ل-س","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ل-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20416"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"docile, obedient, tame"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"sociable, easygoing"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"familiar"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"flexible, smooth (style)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"phlegmatic","tags":["modern"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"suffering from diabetes"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare سَلِسَ (salisa, “to be obedient, to be docile, to be smooth (style)”)."},"ipa":["/sa.lis/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20416","headword_ar":"سَلِسٌ","root":"sls","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisa","text_ar":"سَلِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAlisN","text_ar":"سَالِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Loose, not tight;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slack;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1, first sentence;) and also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsteady;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a nail, (A, TA,) and to any other thing. (TA.) A rájiz says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      mamokuwrapN garovaY Alwi$aAHi Als~aAlisi\n                      \n                     \n                        taDoHaku Eano *iY A^u$ur K guDaArisi"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1405},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A female of slender make, whose loose"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wi$aAH","text_ar":"وِشَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"required more than it had within it to fill it, laughing so as to discover cool and sweet serrated and sharp teeth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Easy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a thing: (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gentle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tractable; submissive; compliant; obsequious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) applied [to a horse and the like, and, tropically,] to a man. (S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN salisu AlqiyaAdi","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ سَلِسُ القِيَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse easy to be led; tractable"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN salisu AlqiyaAdi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ سَلِسُ القِيَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqiyaAdi","text_ar":"القِيَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misolaAsu","text_ar":"مِسْلَاسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is easy to be led,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"persuaded; tractable, submissive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compliant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b3-  (tropical:)  A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy in private conference;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saholu Alxalowapi","text_ar":"سَهْلُ الخَلْوَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b4-  Beverage, or wine,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that descends gently"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easily"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"down the throat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salisu Albawoli","text_ar":"سَلِسُ البَوْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose urine flows involuntarily; who is unable to retain his urine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of disease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["M","A","TA","S","Msb","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}